      "writtenOn": "2019-08-01T19:24:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "from this doc it is unclear to me what are the recommendation for this value, or what is the intention. What values do you anticipate?\n\nif \"stable\", then seems to imply that we\u0027d build and mark at stable at the same time? this sounds risky to me: we\u0027d first need to verify that it is indeed stable (build image, push to staging, see how it behaves there), and only then mark it as stable (without rebuilding)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "0852fcdbbdaf0d92df8707c81aab4e86cde01488",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "183cb9ec_2699473e",
        "filename": "results/README.md",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 16,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-01T20:46:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right now, tagging with \"stable\" is meant to be done in `make deploy`, so `image-label` is just whatever description with which the user wants to annotate.\n\nFor instance, let\u0027s say I have two branches with changes FOO (with commit hash f00d) and BAR (with commit hash baad) committed, respectively. I might label them `with-change-foo` and `with-change-bar`, and they\u0027d both /also/ be tagged `f00d` and `baad`, respectively.\n\nThen on deployment, if I decided I wanted to deploy f00d, I could say `make deploy LABEL\u003dwith-change-foo`.\n\nThese retagging shenanigans aren\u0027t fantastic.\n\nVadim mentioned manually changing the deployment, specifically, \"[via] manual commit to the repository with k8s configs\". I can adapt that into here by getting rid of the \"stable\" label.\n\nThoughts?",
      "parentUuid": "8f32717e_f4c6957a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "0852fcdbbdaf0d92df8707c81aab4e86cde01488",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "043ae2df_610d4bba",
        "filename": "results/README.md",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 16,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-01T22:14:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i see the intention now. I see the value in LABEL parameter for specifying what to deploy.\n\nI don\u0027t see value of LABEL parameter in other scenarios: we could use the label derived from `get-rev HEAD` to identify the version. It matches your use case (foo, f00d, baad), already implemented and does not require extra typing. So I think LABEL is unnecessary for building and pushing images.\n\ni suspect using a concrete tag (not stable) would be more useful. In https://pantheon.corp.google.com/kubernetes/deployment/us-central1-a/ingestion-cluster/default/recorder-service?project\u003dluci-test-results-dev\u0026tab\u003dhistory\u0026deployment_overview_active_revisions_tablesize\u003d50\u0026duration\u003dPT1H\u0026pod_summary_list_tablesize\u003d20\u0026service_list_datatablesize\u003d20\u0026deployment_revision_history_tablesize\u003d50 I see a list of pod revisions, but each revision does not tell me which git revision was used.\n\nVadim, please note this ^ I assume using revision-based tags in yaml files will solve this problem, since I see \"stable\" in that list",
      "parentUuid": "183cb9ec_2699473e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "0852fcdbbdaf0d92df8707c81aab4e86cde01488",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9a0c1a5e_a1a7a6ca",
        "filename": "results/README.md",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 16,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-02T03:09:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In accordance with using a concrete tag for deployment, I\u0027ve gotten rid of the stable tag, both in Makefile and recorder-deployment.yaml.\n\nThis consequently means the `deploy` target no longer accepts a LABEL, and gets rid of the `all` target.\n\nI\u0027ve also gotten rid of LABEL for building and pushing images (that means no manual descriptions for distinguishing two images with side-by-side changes at a glance, but we can add that back later if we want). Note that IMAGE_ID can still be overwritten if passed to make, in which case the image will /not/ be tagged with \u003chash\u003e-tainted.\n\nDoes that match what you mean?",
      "parentUuid": "043ae2df_610d4bba",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "0852fcdbbdaf0d92df8707c81aab4e86cde01488",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
